---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PrivateHeader from "../../components/PrivateHeader.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const linkedinRecommendationUrl = "https://www.linkedin.com/in/leigh-ann-martin/edit/forms/recommendation/write";

const contacts = [
  {
    name: "Dr. Pete Salzmann",
    title: "Former CEO",
    company: "Immunovant",
    relationship: "Leigh-Ann was Pete's Senior Executive Assistant for ~5 years, supporting him through clinical-stage transitions, board governance, and investor relations.",
    email: "pete.salzmann@immunovant.com",
    altEmails: [],
    recommendation: `Leigh-Ann was my right hand for five years at Immunovant. She managed every aspect of my executive operations, from board meeting preparation to investor correspondence across 200+ stakeholders. What set her apart was her ability to anticipate what I needed before I asked. During our clinical-stage transitions, when the pace of regulatory meetings, investor updates, and board communications accelerated dramatically, Leigh-Ann kept everything running without a single missed deadline. She handled confidential matters with absolute discretion and built operational systems that outlasted any single initiative. I would recommend her without hesitation to any CEO who needs someone they can trust completely.`,
    emailSubject: "A favor I've been meaning to ask",
    emailBody: `Hi Pete,

I hope you're doing well. I've been thinking about our time working together at Immunovant, and I wanted to ask you something.

I'm building my fractional executive support practice and LinkedIn recommendations from people I've worked closely with would mean a lot. You saw my work firsthand for five years, and a recommendation from you would carry real weight.

I know writing these from scratch can be a pain, so I drafted something below based on our work together. You're welcome to use it as-is, edit it to match your voice, or write something completely different. Whatever feels right.

Here's the draft:

---

"Leigh-Ann was my right hand for five years at Immunovant. She managed every aspect of my executive operations, from board meeting preparation to investor correspondence across 200+ stakeholders. What set her apart was her ability to anticipate what I needed before I asked. During our clinical-stage transitions, when the pace of regulatory meetings, investor updates, and board communications accelerated dramatically, Leigh-Ann kept everything running without a single missed deadline. She handled confidential matters with absolute discretion and built operational systems that outlasted any single initiative. I would recommend her without hesitation to any CEO who needs someone they can trust completely."

---

Here's the direct link to leave the recommendation on LinkedIn:
${linkedinRecommendationUrl}

No pressure at all. I appreciate you either way.

Warmly,
Leigh-Ann`
  },
  {
    name: "Renee Barnett",
    title: "Former CFO",
    company: "Immunovant",
    relationship: "Leigh-Ann worked closely with Renee on financial reporting, board materials, investor communications, and SEC filing coordination during their overlapping tenure at Immunovant (2021-2024).",
    email: "renee.barnett@immunovant.com",
    altEmails: [],
    recommendation: `I worked alongside Leigh-Ann for several years at Immunovant, and she was one of the most reliable operational partners I've had. As CFO, I depended on precise coordination for board materials, quarterly reporting, and investor communications. Leigh-Ann managed all of it with exceptional attention to detail. She understood the cadence of a publicly traded company and never let a deadline slip. What impressed me most was her financial literacy. She didn't just move documents around. She understood what was in them and flagged issues before they became problems. Any executive team would be lucky to have her.`,
    emailSubject: "Quick request from a former Immunovant colleague",
    emailBody: `Hi Renee,

I hope all is well! I've been thinking about our time at Immunovant and wanted to reach out with a small ask.

I'm growing my fractional executive support business and building out my LinkedIn presence. A recommendation from you would mean a great deal, especially given how closely we worked on board materials, investor communications, and quarterly reporting.

I drafted something below to make it easy. Feel free to use it, adjust it, or write your own. Whatever works for you.

Here's the draft:

---

"I worked alongside Leigh-Ann for several years at Immunovant, and she was one of the most reliable operational partners I've had. As CFO, I depended on precise coordination for board materials, quarterly reporting, and investor communications. Leigh-Ann managed all of it with exceptional attention to detail. She understood the cadence of a publicly traded company and never let a deadline slip. What impressed me most was her financial literacy. She didn't just move documents around. She understood what was in them and flagged issues before they became problems. Any executive team would be lucky to have her."

---

Here's the direct link to leave the recommendation on LinkedIn:
${linkedinRecommendationUrl}

Thank you so much, Renee. I really appreciate it.

Warmly,
Leigh-Ann`
  },
  {
    name: "John Hartmann",
    title: "Former CEO",
    company: "Ascend Wellness Holdings",
    relationship: "Leigh-Ann served as EA and Investor Relations support to John during his tenure as CEO (2023-2024), managing operations across 7 markets and 48 retail locations.",
    email: "john.hartmann@awholdings.com",
    altEmails: [],
    recommendation: `Leigh-Ann supported me as EA and Investor Relations coordinator at Ascend Wellness Holdings during a period of significant operational growth. She managed stakeholder relationships across seven markets and kept investor communications running smoothly for a publicly traded, multi-state cannabis operation. What stood out was her ability to operate in a highly regulated, fast-moving environment without missing a beat. Board preparation, investor updates, compliance-sensitive communications. She handled it all with professionalism and discretion. Leigh-Ann is the kind of executive partner who makes the entire leadership team more effective.`,
    emailSubject: "A small favor, John",
    emailBody: `Hi John,

I hope the new chapter is going well. I wanted to reach out because I've been building my fractional executive support practice, and a LinkedIn recommendation from you would be incredibly valuable.

You saw firsthand what I brought to Ascend, from investor relations across 7 markets to board prep and stakeholder management. Your perspective on that work would mean a lot to prospective clients.

I've drafted something below to save you time. Feel free to use it, tweak it, or write something entirely your own.

Here's the draft:

