  {
    name: "Dan Neville",
    title: "Former CFO & Interim Co-CEO",
    company: "Ascend Wellness Holdings",
    relationship: "Leigh-Ann worked closely with Dan on financial reporting, investor communications, and quarterly operations during the company's time as a publicly traded entity.",
    email: "dan.neville@awholdings.com",
    altEmails: [],
    recommendation: `Working with Leigh-Ann at Ascend Wellness was a genuinely positive experience. On the finance and investor relations side, she was meticulous. Quarterly reporting, board materials, stakeholder updates. Everything was accurate, on time, and well-organized. For a publicly traded company navigating a complex regulatory landscape across multiple states, that level of precision matters. Leigh-Ann also brought emotional intelligence to the role. She understood the pressures facing the leadership team and found ways to reduce friction rather than add to it. I'd recommend her to any executive who needs a trusted operational partner.`,
    emailSubject: "Quick ask from Leigh-Ann",
    emailBody: `Hi Dan,

I hope you're doing well. I've been building my fractional executive support practice and wanted to ask if you'd be willing to write a brief LinkedIn recommendation for me.

We worked closely on the finance and investor relations side at Ascend, and your perspective on that work would be really meaningful to prospective clients.

I drafted something below to make it as easy as possible. Feel free to use it, change it, or write your own version.

Here's the draft:

